.272000000000000000,"sox":0.158547784404513840,"noxMt":2.720000000000000600,"nox":1.585477844045138700,"euEtsDetails":null}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2021-09-08T07:01:07.75","modifiedByFull":"Dragheim, Carsten Bo","remark":"Jan/Feb/Mar bunker hedge value 36k (income) removed as voy is not COA"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-03-03T23:12:20.013","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Voyage generated 1:1 so quite a bit different than the pre-calc.\n\u2022\tLake Charles (2 berths) \u002B Texas City added as loadports against $105k lumpsum\no\tThis increased LSGO consumption by $16k\n\u2022\tDamietta/Adabiya 2 add\u2019l disports Egypt added against $120k lumpsum\no\tChartering note \u2013 calling ports in Med/Egypt forfeits our Suez Canal rebate.  Something to consider moving forward when negotiating these lumpsum rates.\n\u2022\tMundra/Kandla 2 add\u2019l disports WCI added against $100k lumpsum\no\tActual cost $130k plus steaming\n\u2022\tGuards est $20k but actual $7300 due to short stay onboard\n\u2022\tHFO consumption up $66k due to extended voyage/extra ports\n\u2022\t23 add\u2019l port days, less 5 days laytime and a few longer pilotages at Pt. Comfort/LKC, we netted 18 days on demurrage at a great rate $24k/day adding $440k to the result.\n\u2022\tHire was reduced from $17,250 to $15750 halfway through voyage which reduced overall hire expense by about $50k.\nOPS NOTE \u2013 We were mega tight on laycan to start the voyage.  Wisby pushed class for an extension to UWS intermediate exam and allowed us to sail last disport without delay.  The vessel cleaned all tanks to strict WWT spec in 6 days.  During the cleaning, they had a pump failure and vessel C/E was able to repair with onboard fabricated piece when even the pump manufacturer told them they wouldn\u2019t be able to do it.  All in all, they cleaned/passed WWT/made the laycan on Christmas day.  Not only a present for us, but charterers as well.  Quite pleased with Wisby as a partner during this voyage."},{"modifiedDate":"2021-01-14T17:10:56.387","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Hire reduced from 17250 to 15750 on 24JAN"},{"modifiedDate":"2021-01-14T17:02:08.707","modifiedByFull":"Ervasti, Josh","remark":"Vessel Hire reduced from 17,250 to $15750 on 24JAN - avg hire estimated"},{"modifiedDate":"2020-12-11T18:23:43.74","modifiedByFull":"ErikssonF, Fredrik","remark":"Charter Party Date:                                November 09, 2020\n\nOwner:                                                 STENA BULK A/S\n\nCharterer:                                             Kolmar Americas, Inc.\n \nVessel:                                                M/T Wisby Atlantic/OOS or M/T Wisby Pacific/OOS  (Ship to always have valid SIRE/CDI and to have major approvals and be acceptable to  GPRE/Eco Energy/Valero/Murex)\n \nCargo(s)                                             Min 39kt (basis 38ft FW max vessel draft) up to full cargo (sub max vessel drafts) Chemical use Ethanol and or EDC and/or SM or other products on \n                                                           vessel COF and coating manufacturers recommendation, to be mutually agreed. \n                                                         (Owner warrant min 39kt intake basis 38ft FW max vessel draft)\n                                                         *** Ethanol Cargo will need to be denatured with 5-6ppm Bitrex (denatonium benzoate or denatonium saccharide or similar)\n                                                         added to cargo via tank hatches while vessel bunkers at Gibraltar or while vessel transits Suez Canal.***\n            \nLaycan:                                               December 16-25, 2020 Laycan to be narrowed to a 10 day window by owners latest 15 days prior to laycan commencement and further narrowed to a 7 day window 7 days prior to commencement of \n                                                         newly narrowed laycan  \n \nLoadport(s):                                        TX Gulf Coast-MS River range \n \nDischarge Port(s):                                Damietta and/or Adabiyah and/or WCI  Mumba-Kandla range\n \nLaytime:                                              120 hrs \n \nDemurrage:                                         US$24,000 PDPR \n \nFreight (min 39kt on 38ft FW):               US$,1,675,000 1/1 \n \nAdditional loadport(s) USG          \nExc. MS River:                                      US$45k LS all inclusive \nAdditional berth (same port)                   US$15k LS all inclusive\nDamietta                                             US$70k LS all inclusive  \nAdabiyah                                             US$50k LS all inclusive  \nWCI (Mumba-Kandla range)                  US$50K LS all inclusive"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}